{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SwmL85eKYJgvy1twBSg33H","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.repository;\n     2→\n     3→import com.example.orderspring.entity.Part;\n     4→import com.example.orderspring.entity.PartKey;\n     5→import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository;\n     6→import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Query;\n     7→import org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→import java.util.Optional;\n    11→\n    12→@Repository\n    13→public interface PartRepository extends JpaRepository<Part, PartKey> {\n    14→    \n    15→    @Query(\"SELECT p FROM Part p ORDER BY p.partNumber\")\n    16→    List<Part> findAllParts();\n    17→    \n    18→    Optional<Part> findByPartNumberAndRevision(String partNumber, int revision);\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"5e610365-7dc7-49f5-8847-cb225e3cd888"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Yax7r23AzXZZEqNUVMBq1P","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.repository;\n     2→\n     3→import com.example.orderspring.entity.Vendor;\n     4→import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository;\n     5→import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Query;\n     6→import org.springframework.data.repository.query.Param;\n     7→import org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→\n    11→@Repository\n    12→public interface VendorRepository extends JpaRepository<Vendor, Integer> {\n    13→    \n    14→    @Query(\"SELECT v FROM Vendor v WHERE LOCATE(:name, v.name) > 0\")\n    15→    List<Vendor> findVendorsByPartialName(@Param(\"name\") String name);\n    16→    \n    17→    @Query(\"SELECT DISTINCT l.vendorPart.vendor FROM CustomerOrder co, IN(co.lineItems) l WHERE co.orderId = :id ORDER BY l.vendorPart.vendor.name\")\n    18→    List<Vendor> findVendorByCustomerOrder(@Param(\"id\") Integer orderId);\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"c11febdd-2fa1-4449-b52d-9c19f77129e3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XjQhwdPouMsv7DaRNwrMpo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.repository;\n     2→\n     3→import com.example.orderspring.entity.VendorPart;\n     4→import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository;\n     5→import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Query;\n     6→import org.springframework.data.repository.query.Param;\n     7→import org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→\n    11→@Repository\n    12→public interface VendorPartRepository extends JpaRepository<VendorPart, Long> {\n    13→    \n    14→    @Query(\"SELECT AVG(vp.price) FROM VendorPart vp\")\n    15→    Double findAverageVendorPartPrice();\n    16→    \n    17→    @Query(\"SELECT SUM(vp.price) FROM VendorPart vp WHERE vp.vendor.vendorId = :id\")\n    18→    Double findTotalVendorPartPricePerVendor(@Param(\"id\") int vendorId);\n    19→    \n    20→    @Query(\"SELECT vp FROM VendorPart vp ORDER BY vp.vendorPartNumber\")\n    21→    List<VendorPart> findAllVendorParts();\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"bbaa3aff-abb5-43b4-a5a2-2b89c5a993cc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015E9xpuixmKCSFE7sQ2qCZo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.service;\n     2→\n     3→import com.example.orderspring.entity.*;\n     4→import com.example.orderspring.repository.*;\n     5→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     6→import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\n     7→import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n     8→\n     9→import java.io.Serializable;\n    10→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    11→import java.util.Collection;\n    12→import java.util.Iterator;\n    13→import java.util.List;\n    14→import java.util.logging.Level;\n    15→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    16→\n    17→@Service\n    18→@Transactional\n    19→public class OrderService {\n    20→    \n    21→    @Autowired\n    22→    private PartRepository partRepository;\n    23→    \n    24→    @Autowired\n    25→    private CustomerOrderRepository customerOrderRepository;\n    26→    \n    27→    @Autowired\n    28→    private VendorRepository vendorRepository;\n    29→    \n    30→    @Autowired\n    31→    private VendorPartRepository vendorPartRepository;\n    32→    \n    33→    @Autowired\n    34→    private LineItemRepository lineItemRepository;\n    35→    \n    36→    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(\"order.service.OrderService\");\n    37→    \n    38→    public void createPart(String partNumber, int revision, String description, \n    39→                          java.util.Date revisionDate, String specification, Serializable drawing) {\n    40→        try {\n    41→            Part part = new Part(partNumber, revision, description, revisionDate, specification, drawing);\n    42→            logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Created part {0}-{1}\", new Object[]{partNumber, revision});\n    43→            partRepository.save(part);\n    44→            logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Persisted part {0}-{1}\", new Object[]{partNumber, revision});\n    45→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n    46→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error creating part\", ex);\n    47→            throw new RuntimeException(ex.getMessage());\n    48→        }\n    49→    }\n    50→\n    51→    public List<Part> getAllParts() {\n    52→        return partRepository.findAllParts();\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    public void addPartToBillOfMaterial(String bomPartNumber, int bomRevision, \n    56→                                       String partNumber, int revision) {\n    57→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"BOM part number: {0}\", bomPartNumber);\n    58→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"BOM revision: {0}\", bomRevision);\n    59→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Part number: {0}\", partNumber);\n    60→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Part revision: {0}\", revision);\n    61→        try {\n    62→            PartKey bomKey = new PartKey();\n    63→            bomKey.setPartNumber(bomPartNumber);\n    64→            bomKey.setRevision(bomRevision);\n    65→            \n    66→            Part bom = partRepository.findByPartNumberAndRevision(bomPartNumber, bomRevision).orElse(null);\n    67→            if (bom != null) {\n    68→                logger.log(Level.INFO, \"BOM Part found: {0}\", bom.getPartNumber());\n    69→                \n    70→                Part part = partRepository.findByPartNumberAndRevision(partNumber, revision).orElse(null);\n    71→                if (part != null) {\n    72→                    logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Part found: {0}\", part.getPartNumber());\n    73→                    bom.getParts().add(part);\n    74→                    part.setBomPart(bom);\n    75→                    partRepository.save(bom);\n    76→                    partRepository.save(part);\n    77→                }\n    78→            }\n    79→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    80→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error adding part to BOM\", e);\n    81→        }\n    82→    }\n    83→    \n    84→    public void createVendor(int vendorId, String name, String address, String contact, String phone) {\n    85→        try {\n    86→            Vendor vendor = new Vendor(vendorId, name, address, contact, phone);\n    87→            vendorRepository.save(vendor);\n    88→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    89→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error creating vendor\", e);\n    90→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n    91→        }\n    92→    }\n    93→    \n    94→    public void createVendorPart(String partNumber, int revision, String description, \n    95→                                double price, int vendorId) {\n    96→        try {\n    97→            Part part = partRepository.findByPartNumberAndRevision(partNumber, revision).orElse(null);\n    98→            if (part != null) {\n    99→                VendorPart vendorPart = new VendorPart(description, price, part);\n   100→                vendorPartRepository.save(vendorPart);\n   101→                \n   102→                Vendor vendor = vendorRepository.findById(vendorId).orElse(null);\n   103→                if (vendor != null) {\n   104→                    vendor.addVendorPart(vendorPart);\n   105→                    vendorPart.setVendor(vendor);\n   106→                    vendorRepository.save(vendor);\n   107→                    vendorPartRepository.save(vendorPart);\n   108→                }\n   109→            }\n   110→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   111→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error creating vendor part\", e);\n   112→            throw new RuntimeException(e.getMessage());\n   113→        }\n   114→    }\n   115→    \n   116→    @Transactional\n   117→    public void createOrder(Integer orderId, char status, int discount, String shipmentInfo) {\n   118→        if (orderId == null) throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Order ID is required\");\n   119→        if (customerOrderRepository.existsById(orderId)) {\n   120→            throw new IllegalStateException(\"Order ID \" + orderId + \" already exists\");\n   121→        }\n   122→        customerOrderRepository.save(new CustomerOrder(orderId, status, discount, shipmentInfo));\n   123→    }\n   124→\n   125→    public List<CustomerOrder> getOrders() {\n   126→        try {\n   127→            return customerOrderRepository.findAllOrders();\n   128→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   129→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error getting orders\", e);\n   130→            throw new RuntimeException(e.getMessage());\n   131→        }\n   132→    }\n   133→    \n   134→    public void addLineItem(Integer orderId, String partNumber, int revision, int quantity) {\n   135→        try {\n   136→            CustomerOrder order = customerOrderRepository.findById(orderId).orElse(null);\n   137→            if (order != null) {\n   138→                logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Found order ID {0}\", orderId);\n   139→                \n   140→                Part part = partRepository.findByPartNumberAndRevision(partNumber, revision).orElse(null);\n   141→                if (part != null && part.getVendorPart() != null) {\n   142→                    LineItem lineItem = new LineItem(order, quantity, part.getVendorPart());\n   143→                    order.addLineItem(lineItem);\n   144→                    lineItemRepository.save(lineItem);\n   145→                    customerOrderRepository.save(order);\n   146→                }\n   147→            }\n   148→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   149→            logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Couldn't add {0} to order ID {1}.\", new Object[]{partNumber, orderId});\n   150→            throw new RuntimeException(e.getMessage());\n   151→        }\n   152→    }\n   153→    \n   154→    public double getBillOfMaterialPrice(String bomPartNumber, int bomRevision, \n   155→                                       String partNumber, int revision) {\n   156→        double price = 0.0;\n   157→        try {\n   158→            Part bom = partRepository.findByPartNumberAndRevision(bomPartNumber, bomRevision).orElse(null);\n   159→            if (bom != null) {\n   160→                Collection<Part> parts = bom.getParts();\n   161→                for (Part part : parts) {\n   162→                    VendorPart vendorPart = part.getVendorPart();\n   163→                    if (vendorPart != null) {\n   164→                        price += vendorPart.getPrice();\n   165→                    }\n   166→                }\n   167→            }\n   168→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   169→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error calculating BOM price\", e);\n   170→            throw new RuntimeException(e.getMessage());\n   171→        }\n   172→        return price;\n   173→    }\n   174→    \n   175→    public double getOrderPrice(Integer orderId) {\n   176→        double price = 0.0;\n   177→        try {\n   178→            CustomerOrder order = customerOrderRepository.findById(orderId).orElse(null);\n   179→            if (order != null) {\n   180→                price = order.calculateAmount();\n   181→            }\n   182→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   183→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error calculating order price\", e);\n   184→            throw new RuntimeException(e.getMessage());\n   185→        }\n   186→        return price;\n   187→    }\n   188→    \n   189→    public void adjustOrderDiscount(int adjustment) {\n   190→        try {\n   191→            List<CustomerOrder> orders = customerOrderRepository.findAllOrders();\n   192→            for (CustomerOrder order : orders) {\n   193→                int newDiscount = order.getDiscount() + adjustment;\n   194→                order.setDiscount((newDiscount > 0) ? newDiscount : 0);\n   195→                customerOrderRepository.save(order);\n   196→            }\n   197→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   198→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error adjusting order discount\", e);\n   199→            throw new RuntimeException(e.getMessage());\n   200→        }\n   201→    }\n   202→    \n   203→    public Double getAvgPrice() {\n   204→        try {\n   205→            return vendorPartRepository.findAverageVendorPartPrice();\n   206→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   207→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error getting average price\", e);\n   208→            throw new RuntimeException(e.getMessage());\n   209→        }\n   210→    }\n   211→    \n   212→    public Double getTotalPricePerVendor(int vendorId) {\n   213→        try {\n   214→            return vendorPartRepository.findTotalVendorPartPricePerVendor(vendorId);\n   215→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   216→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error getting total price per vendor\", e);\n   217→            throw new RuntimeException(e.getMessage());\n   218→        }\n   219→    }\n   220→    \n   221→    public List<String> locateVendorsByPartialName(String name) {\n   222→        List<String> names = new ArrayList<>();\n   223→        try {\n   224→            List<Vendor> vendors = vendorRepository.findVendorsByPartialName(name);\n   225→            for (Vendor vendor : vendors) {\n   226→                names.add(vendor.getName());\n   227→            }\n   228→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   229→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error locating vendors\", e);\n   230→            throw new RuntimeException(e.getMessage());\n   231→        }\n   232→        return names;\n   233→    }\n   234→    \n   235→    public int countAllItems() {\n   236→        int count = 0;\n   237→        try {\n   238→            count = lineItemRepository.findAllLineItems().size();\n   239→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   240→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error counting items\", e);\n   241→            throw new RuntimeException(e.getMessage());\n   242→        }\n   243→        return count;\n   244→    }\n   245→\n   246→    public List<LineItem> getLineItems(int orderId) {\n   247→        try {\n   248→            return lineItemRepository.findLineItemsByOrderId(orderId);\n   249→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   250→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error getting line items\", e);\n   251→            throw new RuntimeException(e.getMessage());\n   252→        }\n   253→    }\n   254→    \n   255→    @Transactional\n   256→    public void removeOrder(Integer orderId) {\n   257→        lineItemRepository.deleteAllByOrderId(orderId);\n   258→        customerOrderRepository.deleteById(orderId);\n   259→    }\n   260→    \n   261→    public String reportVendorsByOrder(Integer orderId) {\n   262→        StringBuilder report = new StringBuilder();\n   263→        try {\n   264→            List<Vendor> vendors = vendorRepository.findVendorByCustomerOrder(orderId);\n   265→            for (Vendor vendor : vendors) {\n   266→                report.append(vendor.getVendorId()).append(' ')\n   267→                        .append(vendor.getName()).append(' ')\n   268→                        .append(vendor.getContact()).append('\\n');\n   269→            }\n   270→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   271→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error reporting vendors by order\", e);\n   272→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n   273→        }\n   274→        return report.toString();\n   275→    }\n   276→    \n   277→    // Additional methods for JSF integration\n   278→    public List<CustomerOrder> getAllOrders() {\n   279→        return getOrders();\n   280→    }\n   281→    \n   282→    public List<LineItem> getLineItemsByOrderId(Integer orderId) {\n   283→        return getLineItems(orderId);\n   284→    }\n   285→    \n   286→    public List<Vendor> findVendorsByName(String name) {\n   287→        try {\n   288→            return vendorRepository.findVendorsByPartialName(name);\n   289→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   290→            logger.log(Level.SEVERE, \"Error finding vendors by name\", e);\n   291→            throw new RuntimeException(e.getMessage());\n   292→        }\n   293→    }\n   294→}\n   295→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"32a42772-5cc3-4a83-a8ab-6f95481564b1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012pokFfXfxs4LqG5AH9UJE6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.service;\n     2→\n     3→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     4→import org.springframework.boot.context.event.ApplicationReadyEvent;\n     5→import org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\n     6→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n     7→import java.io.Serializable;\n     8→import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n     9→\n    10→@Component\n    11→public class DataInitializationService {\n    12→    \n    13→    @Autowired\n    14→    private OrderService orderService;\n    15→    \n    16→    @EventListener(ApplicationReadyEvent.class)\n    17→    @Transactional\n    18→    public void onApplicationReady() {\n    19→        createInitialData();\n    20→    }\n    21→    \n    22→    private void createInitialData() {\n    23→        // Create parts\n    24→        orderService.createPart(\"1234-5678-01\", 1, \"ABC PART\",\n    25→                new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    26→        orderService.createPart(\"9876-4321-02\", 2, \"DEF PART\",\n    27→                new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    28→        orderService.createPart(\"5456-6789-03\", 3, \"GHI PART\",\n    29→                new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    30→        orderService.createPart(\"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, \"XYZ PART\",\n    31→                new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    32→        orderService.createPart(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"BOM PART\",\n    33→                new java.util.Date(), \"PARTQWERTYUIOPASXDCFVGBHNJMKL\", null);\n    34→\n    35→        // Add parts to bill of materials\n    36→        orderService.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"1234-5678-01\", 1);\n    37→        orderService.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"9876-4321-02\", 2);\n    38→        orderService.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"5456-6789-03\", 3);\n    39→        orderService.addPartToBillOfMaterial(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5);\n    40→\n    41→        // Create vendors\n    42→        orderService.createVendor(100, \"WidgetCorp\",\n    43→                \"111 Main St., Anytown, KY 99999\", \"Mr. Jones\",\n    44→                \"888-777-9999\");\n    45→        orderService.createVendor(200, \"Gadget, Inc.\",\n    46→                \"123 State St., Sometown, MI 88888\", \"Mrs. Smith\",\n    47→                \"866-345-6789\");\n    48→\n    49→        // Create vendor parts\n    50→        orderService.createVendorPart(\"1234-5678-01\", 1, \"PART1\", 100.00, 100);\n    51→        orderService.createVendorPart(\"9876-4321-02\", 2, \"PART2\", 10.44, 200);\n    52→        orderService.createVendorPart(\"5456-6789-03\", 3, \"PART3\", 76.23, 200);\n    53→        orderService.createVendorPart(\"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, \"PART4\", 55.19, 100);\n    54→        orderService.createVendorPart(\"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, \"PART5\", 345.87, 100);\n    55→\n    56→        // Create orders\n    57→        Integer orderId = 1111;\n    58→        orderService.createOrder(orderId, 'N', 10, \"333 New Court, New City, CA 90000\");\n    59→        orderService.addLineItem(orderId, \"1234-5678-01\", 1, 3);\n    60→        orderService.addLineItem(orderId, \"9876-4321-02\", 2, 5);\n    61→        orderService.addLineItem(orderId, \"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, 7);\n    62→\n    63→        orderId = 4312;\n    64→        orderService.createOrder(orderId, 'N', 0, \"333 New Court, New City, CA 90000\");\n    65→        orderService.addLineItem(orderId, \"SDFG-ERTY-BN\", 7, 1);\n    66→        orderService.addLineItem(orderId, \"ABCD-XYZW-FF\", 5, 3);\n    67→        orderService.addLineItem(orderId, \"1234-5678-01\", 1, 15);\n    68→    }\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"6fc2e175-93d9-4f85-8767-348c6a05dc89"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CUeQBzRcQCiV52wKGN6iWP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring;\n     2→\n     3→import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\n     4→import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\n     5→\n     6→@SpringBootApplication\n     7→public class OrderApplication {\n     8→\n     9→    public static void main(String[] args) {\n    10→        SpringApplication.run(OrderApplication.class, args);\n    11→    }\n    12→}\n    13→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"b2d593ee-9e2d-4e7a-af3b-5c916a8e2f42"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FKnUphCQXvj7RMfx72omcW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.web;\n     2→\n     3→import com.example.orderspring.entity.CustomerOrder;\n     4→import com.example.orderspring.entity.LineItem;\n     5→import com.example.orderspring.entity.Part;\n     6→import com.example.orderspring.entity.Vendor;\n     7→import com.example.orderspring.service.OrderService;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.context.SessionScoped;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    10→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    11→import jakarta.faces.context.FacesContext;\n    12→import jakarta.faces.event.ActionEvent;\n    13→import java.io.Serializable;\n    14→import java.util.List;\n    15→\n    16→@Named(\"orderManager\")\n    17→@SessionScoped\n    18→public class OrderManager implements Serializable {\n    19→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    20→\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private OrderService orderService;\n    23→\n    24→    private List<CustomerOrder> orders;\n    25→    private List<LineItem> lineItems;\n    26→    private List<Part> parts;\n    27→    private List<Vendor> vendorSearchResults;\n    28→\n    29→    private Integer currentOrder;\n    30→    private Integer newOrderId;\n    31→    private String newOrderShippingInfo;\n    32→    private Character newOrderStatus = 'P';\n    33→    private Integer newOrderDiscount = 0;\n    34→    private String vendorName;\n    35→    private boolean findVendorTableDisabled = true;\n    36→    \n    37→    private List<Part> newOrderParts;\n    38→    private String selectedPartNumber;\n    39→    private Integer selectedPartRevision;\n    40→    private Long selectedVendorPartNumber;\n    41→\n    42→    public List<CustomerOrder> getOrders() {\n    43→        if (orders == null) {\n    44→            orders = orderService.getAllOrders();\n    45→        }\n    46→        return orders;\n    47→    }\n    48→    public void setOrders(List<CustomerOrder> orders) { this.orders = orders; }\n    49→\n    50→    public List<LineItem> getLineItems() {\n    51→        if (lineItems == null && currentOrder != null) {\n    52→            lineItems = orderService.getLineItemsByOrderId(currentOrder);\n    53→        }\n    54→        return lineItems;\n    55→    }\n    56→    public void setLineItems(List<LineItem> lineItems) { this.lineItems = lineItems; }\n    57→\n    58→    public List<Part> getParts() {\n    59→        if (parts == null) {\n    60→            parts = orderService.getAllParts();\n    61→        }\n    62→        return parts;\n    63→    }\n    64→    public void setParts(List<Part> parts) { this.parts = parts; }\n    65→\n    66→    public List<Vendor> getVendorSearchResults() { return vendorSearchResults; }\n    67→    public void setVendorSearchResults(List<Vendor> vendorSearchResults) { this.vendorSearchResults = vendorSearchResults; }\n    68→\n    69→    public Integer getCurrentOrder() { return currentOrder; }\n    70→    public void setCurrentOrder(Integer currentOrder) {\n    71→        this.currentOrder = currentOrder;\n    72→        this.lineItems = null;\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    public Integer getNewOrderId() { return newOrderId; }\n    76→    public void setNewOrderId(Integer newOrderId) { this.newOrderId = newOrderId; }\n    77→\n    78→    public String getNewOrderShippingInfo() { return newOrderShippingInfo; }\n    79→    public void setNewOrderShippingInfo(String newOrderShippingInfo) { this.newOrderShippingInfo = newOrderShippingInfo; }\n    80→\n    81→    public Character getNewOrderStatus() { return newOrderStatus; }\n    82→    public void setNewOrderStatus(Character newOrderStatus) { this.newOrderStatus = newOrderStatus; }\n    83→\n    84→    public Integer getNewOrderDiscount() { return newOrderDiscount; }\n    85→    public void setNewOrderDiscount(Integer newOrderDiscount) { this.newOrderDiscount = newOrderDiscount; }\n    86→\n    87→    public String getVendorName() { return vendorName; }\n    88→    public void setVendorName(String vendorName) { this.vendorName = vendorName; }\n    89→\n    90→    public boolean isFindVendorTableDisabled() { return findVendorTableDisabled; }\n    91→    public void setFindVendorTableDisabled(boolean findVendorTableDisabled) { this.findVendorTableDisabled = findVendorTableDisabled; }\n    92→\n    93→    public List<Part> getNewOrderParts() {\n    94→        if (newOrderParts == null) {\n    95→            newOrderParts = orderService.getAllParts();\n    96→        }\n    97→        return newOrderParts;\n    98→    }\n    99→    public void setNewOrderParts(List<Part> newOrderParts) { this.newOrderParts = newOrderParts; }\n   100→\n   101→    public String getSelectedPartNumber() { return selectedPartNumber; }\n   102→    public void setSelectedPartNumber(String selectedPartNumber) { this.selectedPartNumber = selectedPartNumber; }\n   103→\n   104→    public Integer getSelectedPartRevision() { return selectedPartRevision; }\n   105→    public void setSelectedPartRevision(Integer selectedPartRevision) { this.selectedPartRevision = selectedPartRevision; }\n   106→\n   107→    public Long getSelectedVendorPartNumber() { return selectedVendorPartNumber; }\n   108→    public void setSelectedVendorPartNumber(Long selectedVendorPartNumber) { this.selectedVendorPartNumber = selectedVendorPartNumber; }\n   109→\n   110→    public String submitOrder() {\n   111→        try {\n   112→            if (newOrderId == null) return \"order\";\n   113→            char status = (newOrderStatus != null ? newOrderStatus : 'P');\n   114→            int discount = (newOrderDiscount != null ? newOrderDiscount : 0);\n   115→            orderService.createOrder(newOrderId, status, discount, newOrderShippingInfo);\n   116→            newOrderId = null;\n   117→            newOrderShippingInfo = null;\n   118→            newOrderStatus = 'P';\n   119→            newOrderDiscount = 0;\n   120→            orders = null;\n   121→            if (currentOrder != null) lineItems = null;\n   122→            return \"order\";\n   123→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   124→            e.printStackTrace();\n   125→            return \"order\";\n   126→        }\n   127→    }\n   128→\n   129→    public String removeOrder() {\n   130→        try {\n   131→            if (currentOrder != null) {\n   132→                orderService.removeOrder(currentOrder);\n   133→                orders = null;\n   134→                lineItems = null;\n   135→                currentOrder = null;\n   136→            }\n   137→            return \"order\";\n   138→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   139→            e.printStackTrace();\n   140→            return \"order\";\n   141→        }\n   142→    }\n   143→\n   144→    public void removeOrder(ActionEvent event) {\n   145→        String id = FacesContext.getCurrentInstance()\n   146→                .getExternalContext()\n   147→                .getRequestParameterMap()\n   148→                .get(\"deleteOrderId\");\n   149→        if (id != null && !id.isBlank()) {\n   150→            Integer orderId = Integer.valueOf(id);\n   151→            orderService.removeOrder(orderId);\n   152→            orders = null;\n   153→            lineItems = null;\n   154→            if (orderId.equals(currentOrder)) currentOrder = null;\n   155→        }\n   156→    }\n   157→\n   158→    public String findVendor() {\n   159→        try {\n   160→            vendorSearchResults = orderService.findVendorsByName(vendorName);\n   161→            findVendorTableDisabled = false;\n   162→            return \"order\";\n   163→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   164→            e.printStackTrace();\n   165→            findVendorTableDisabled = true;\n   166→            return \"order\";\n   167→        }\n   168→    }\n   169→\n   170→    public String addLineItem() {\n   171→        try {\n   172→            if (currentOrder != null && selectedPartNumber != null && selectedPartRevision != null) {\n   173→                orderService.addLineItem(currentOrder, selectedPartNumber, selectedPartRevision, 1);\n   174→                lineItems = null;\n   175→            }\n   176→            return \"lineItem\";\n   177→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   178→            e.printStackTrace();\n   179→            return \"lineItem\";\n   180→        }\n   181→    }\n   182→\n   183→    public String lineItem() { return \"lineItem\"; }\n   184→    public String order() { return \"order\"; }\n   185→}\n   186→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"834206cf-4c6a-4465-ada1-67e564332121"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PqeGFrnuPM7vBkuoNJe9rW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→server.port=8081\n     2→\n     3→spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:testdb\n     4→spring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\n     5→spring.datasource.username=sa\n     6→spring.datasource.password=\n     7→\n     8→spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\n     9→spring.jpa.show-sql=true\n    10→spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.format_sql=true\n    11→\n    12→spring.h2.console.enabled=true\n    13→spring.h2.console.path=/h2-console\n    14→\n    15→joinfaces.faces.PROJECT_STAGE=Development\n    16→joinfaces.primefaces.theme=saga\n    17→\n    18→logging.level.com.example.orderspring=INFO\n    19→logging.level.org.hibernate.SQL=DEBUG\n    20→logging.level.org.hibernate.type.descriptor.sql=TRACE\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"0d4b1e61-febe-4097-9b27-26bef527c5b5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BUwpydByrtFVEqzCm4Do7h","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     6→\n     7→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     8→\n     9→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    10→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    11→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    12→\n    13→# create venv and install\n    14→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    15→\n    16→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    17→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    18→\n    19→# Set working directory\n    20→WORKDIR /app\n    21→\n    22→# Copy all the assets\n    23→COPY . .\n    24→\n    25→RUN if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    26→\n    27→CMD [ \"mvn\", \"clean\", \"package\", \"spring-boot:run\" ]\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"89c97de7-f06a-4613-b502-60a7476be710"}
