{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01QZXwP12mQVHL8nH9ReMsx2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Two issues:\n1. `EntityManager` is `null` in the repository beans - the `@PersistenceContext` injection isn't working in CDI beans (needs `@Transactional` on the calling EJB, or the repos need different management)\n2. The `@PostConstruct` in a `@Singleton @Startup` is rolling back the transaction\n\nThe key issue is that `@PersistenceContext` injection is failing in `@ApplicationScoped` CDI beans. In Jakarta EE, `@PersistenceContext` works in EJBs but requires a managed environment for CDI beans. The solution is to either make the repositories EJBs or use a CDI `@Produces` method for the EntityManager. Let me fix this by making the repositories `@Stateless` EJBs:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3221,"cache_read_input_tokens":131225,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3221,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":811},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"b02a1fef-33ba-48a3-a62e-e7b1efd8726d"}
