{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014hA1iRJTg98DydUcT8WhLb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<persistence version=\"3.0\"\n     3→             xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence\"\n     4→             xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     5→             xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence/persistence_3_0.xsd\">\n     6→\n     7→    <persistence-unit name=\"order-pu\" transaction-type=\"JTA\">\n     8→        <jta-data-source>jdbc/orderDB</jta-data-source>\n     9→        <class>com.example.orderspring.entity.CustomerOrder</class>\n    10→        <class>com.example.orderspring.entity.LineItem</class>\n    11→        <class>com.example.orderspring.entity.Part</class>\n    12→        <class>com.example.orderspring.entity.Vendor</class>\n    13→        <class>com.example.orderspring.entity.VendorPart</class>\n    14→        <properties>\n    15→            <property name=\"jakarta.persistence.schema-generation.database.action\" value=\"drop-and-create\"/>\n    16→            <property name=\"hibernate.show_sql\" value=\"true\"/>\n    17→            <property name=\"hibernate.format_sql\" value=\"true\"/>\n    18→            <property name=\"eclipselink.logging.level.sql\" value=\"FINE\"/>\n    19→            <property name=\"eclipselink.logging.parameters\" value=\"true\"/>\n    20→        </properties>\n    21→    </persistence-unit>\n    22→</persistence>\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"9fdff23c-bea3-4651-b215-4bdcd26ed2a9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01319focixbMELrXzu6NtuZz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.repository;\n     2→\n     3→import com.example.orderspring.entity.CustomerOrder;\n     4→import jakarta.ejb.Stateless;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n     7→\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import java.util.Optional;\n    10→\n    11→@Stateless\n    12→public class CustomerOrderRepository {\n    13→\n    14→    @PersistenceContext(unitName = \"order-pu\")\n    15→    private EntityManager em;\n    16→\n    17→    public List<CustomerOrder> findAllOrders() {\n    18→        return em.createQuery(\"SELECT co FROM CustomerOrder co ORDER BY co.orderId\", CustomerOrder.class)\n    19→                 .getResultList();\n    20→    }\n    21→\n    22→    public Optional<CustomerOrder> findById(Integer id) {\n    23→        CustomerOrder order = em.find(CustomerOrder.class, id);\n    24→        return Optional.ofNullable(order);\n    25→    }\n    26→\n    27→    public boolean existsById(Integer id) {\n    28→        return em.find(CustomerOrder.class, id) != null;\n    29→    }\n    30→\n    31→    public CustomerOrder save(CustomerOrder order) {\n    32→        if (em.find(CustomerOrder.class, order.getOrderId()) == null) {\n    33→            em.persist(order);\n    34→            return order;\n    35→        } else {\n    36→            return em.merge(order);\n    37→        }\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public void deleteById(Integer id) {\n    41→        CustomerOrder order = em.find(CustomerOrder.class, id);\n    42→        if (order != null) {\n    43→            em.remove(em.contains(order) ? order : em.merge(order));\n    44→        }\n    45→    }\n    46→}\n    47→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"c2863969-01a7-4f96-be1c-3caa7d24bc3a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012Tq12z41Ya7gfkw2DJnj39","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.repository;\n     2→\n     3→import com.example.orderspring.entity.LineItem;\n     4→import com.example.orderspring.entity.LineItemKey;\n     5→import jakarta.ejb.Stateless;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→\n    11→@Stateless\n    12→public class LineItemRepository {\n    13→\n    14→    @PersistenceContext(unitName = \"order-pu\")\n    15→    private EntityManager em;\n    16→\n    17→    public List<LineItem> findAllLineItems() {\n    18→        return em.createQuery(\"SELECT l FROM LineItem l\", LineItem.class)\n    19→                 .getResultList();\n    20→    }\n    21→\n    22→    public List<LineItem> findLineItemsByOrderId(Integer orderId) {\n    23→        return em.createQuery(\n    24→                \"SELECT l FROM LineItem l WHERE l.customerOrder.orderId = :orderId ORDER BY l.itemId\",\n    25→                LineItem.class)\n    26→                .setParameter(\"orderId\", orderId)\n    27→                .getResultList();\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    public LineItem findLineItemById(int itemId, Integer orderId) {\n    31→        List<LineItem> results = em.createQuery(\n    32→                \"SELECT DISTINCT l FROM LineItem l WHERE l.itemId = :itemId AND l.customerOrder.orderId = :orderId\",\n    33→                LineItem.class)\n    34→                .setParameter(\"itemId\", itemId)\n    35→                .setParameter(\"orderId\", orderId)\n    36→                .getResultList();\n    37→        return results.isEmpty() ? null : results.get(0);\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public void deleteAllByOrderId(Integer orderId) {\n    41→        em.createQuery(\"DELETE FROM LineItem l WHERE l.customerOrder.orderId = :orderId\")\n    42→          .setParameter(\"orderId\", orderId)\n    43→          .executeUpdate();\n    44→        em.flush();\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    public LineItem save(LineItem lineItem) {\n    48→        LineItem existing = findLineItemById(lineItem.getItemId(),\n    49→            lineItem.getCustomerOrder() != null ? lineItem.getCustomerOrder().getOrderId() : null);\n    50→        if (existing == null) {\n    51→            em.persist(lineItem);\n    52→            return lineItem;\n    53→        } else {\n    54→            return em.merge(lineItem);\n    55→        }\n    56→    }\n    57→}\n    58→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"e12e3741-a94a-40ef-854d-ee1aa164416c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MV8Jg8sRYUUDkYWULbWHDH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\"\"\"\n     2→Smoke tests for the Order Jakarta EE application.\n     3→Tests the REST API endpoints to verify the migration was successful.\n     4→\"\"\"\n     5→import requests\n     6→import sys\n     7→import time\n     8→import os\n     9→\n    10→BASE_URL = os.environ.get(\"BASE_URL\", \"http://localhost:8080\")\n    11→\n    12→def wait_for_app(url, timeout=120):\n    13→    \"\"\"Wait for the application to be ready.\"\"\"\n    14→    start = time.time()\n    15→    while time.time() - start < timeout:\n    16→        try:\n    17→            resp = requests.get(f\"{url}/api/orders/health\", timeout=5)\n    18→            if resp.status_code == 200:\n    19→                print(f\"Application ready after {int(time.time() - start)}s\")\n    20→                return True\n    21→        except requests.exceptions.ConnectionError:\n    22→            pass\n    23→        except requests.exceptions.Timeout:\n    24→            pass\n    25→        time.sleep(2)\n    26→    print(f\"Application did not become ready within {timeout}s\")\n    27→    return False\n    28→\n    29→\n    30→def test_health():\n    31→    \"\"\"Test health endpoint.\"\"\"\n    32→    resp = requests.get(f\"{BASE_URL}/api/orders/health\")\n    33→    assert resp.status_code == 200, f\"Health check failed: {resp.status_code}\"\n    34→    data = resp.json()\n    35→    assert data[\"status\"] == \"UP\", f\"Health status not UP: {data}\"\n    36→    print(\"PASS: health endpoint\")\n    37→\n    38→\n    39→def test_get_orders():\n    40→    \"\"\"Test getting all orders - should have initial data.\"\"\"\n    41→    resp = requests.get(f\"{BASE_URL}/api/orders\")\n    42→    assert resp.status_code == 200, f\"Get orders failed: {resp.status_code}\"\n    43→    data = resp.json()\n    44→    assert isinstance(data, list), f\"Expected list, got {type(data)}\"\n    45→    assert len(data) >= 2, f\"Expected at least 2 orders from init data, got {len(data)}\"\n    46→\n    47→    order_ids = [o[\"orderId\"] for o in data]\n    48→    assert 1111 in order_ids, f\"Order 1111 not found in {order_ids}\"\n    49→    assert 4312 in order_ids, f\"Order 4312 not found in {order_ids}\"\n    50→    print(f\"PASS: get orders ({len(data)} orders found)\")\n    51→\n    52→\n    53→def test_get_order_detail():\n    54→    \"\"\"Test getting a specific order.\"\"\"\n    55→    resp = requests.get(f\"{BASE_URL}/api/orders/1111\")\n    56→    assert resp.status_code == 200, f\"Get order 1111 failed: {resp.status_code}\"\n    57→    data = resp.json()\n    58→    assert data[\"orderId\"] == 1111, f\"Order ID mismatch: {data}\"\n    59→    assert data[\"discount\"] == 10, f\"Discount mismatch: expected 10, got {data['discount']}\"\n    60→    print(\"PASS: get order detail (order 1111)\")\n    61→\n    62→\n    63→def test_get_order_line_items():\n    64→    \"\"\"Test getting line items for order 1111.\"\"\"\n    65→    resp = requests.get(f\"{BASE_URL}/api/orders/1111/lineitems\")\n    66→    assert resp.status_code == 200, f\"Get line items failed: {resp.status_code}\"\n    67→    data = resp.json()\n    68→    assert isinstance(data, list), f\"Expected list, got {type(data)}\"\n    69→    assert len(data) >= 3, f\"Expected at least 3 line items for order 1111, got {len(data)}\"\n    70→    print(f\"PASS: get line items for order 1111 ({len(data)} items)\")\n    71→\n    72→\n    73→def test_get_parts():\n    74→    \"\"\"Test getting all parts.\"\"\"\n    75→    resp = requests.get(f\"{BASE_URL}/api/orders/parts\")\n    76→    assert resp.status_code == 200, f\"Get parts failed: {resp.status_code}\"\n    77→    data = resp.json()\n    78→    assert isinstance(data, list), f\"Expected list, got {type(data)}\"\n    79→    assert len(data) >= 5, f\"Expected at least 5 parts, got {len(data)}\"\n    80→    print(f\"PASS: get parts ({len(data)} parts found)\")\n    81→\n    82→\n    83→def test_search_vendors():\n    84→    \"\"\"Test vendor search.\"\"\"\n    85→    resp = requests.get(f\"{BASE_URL}/api/orders/vendors/search?name=Widget\")\n    86→    assert resp.status_code == 200, f\"Search vendors failed: {resp.status_code}\"\n    87→    data = resp.json()\n    88→    assert isinstance(data, list), f\"Expected list, got {type(data)}\"\n    89→    assert len(data) >= 1, f\"Expected at least 1 vendor matching 'Widget', got {len(data)}\"\n    90→    assert any(\"Widget\" in v[\"name\"] for v in data), f\"No vendor with 'Widget' in name: {data}\"\n    91→    print(f\"PASS: search vendors ({len(data)} found)\")\n    92→\n    93→\n    94→def test_order_not_found():\n    95→    \"\"\"Test 404 for non-existent order.\"\"\"\n    96→    resp = requests.get(f\"{BASE_URL}/api/orders/99999\")\n    97→    assert resp.status_code == 404, f\"Expected 404 for non-existent order, got: {resp.status_code}\"\n    98→    print(\"PASS: order not found returns 404\")\n    99→\n   100→\n   101→def test_jsf_page():\n   102→    \"\"\"Test that the JSF page is accessible.\"\"\"\n   103→    resp = requests.get(f\"{BASE_URL}/order.xhtml\")\n   104→    assert resp.status_code == 200, f\"JSF page failed: {resp.status_code}\"\n   105→    assert \"Order\" in resp.text, f\"JSF page doesn't contain 'Order'\"\n   106→    print(\"PASS: JSF page accessible\")\n   107→\n   108→\n   109→def main():\n   110→    print(f\"Running smoke tests against: {BASE_URL}\")\n   111→\n   112→    if not wait_for_app(BASE_URL):\n   113→        print(\"FAIL: Application did not start\")\n   114→        sys.exit(1)\n   115→\n   116→    tests = [\n   117→        test_health,\n   118→        test_get_orders,\n   119→        test_get_order_detail,\n   120→        test_get_order_line_items,\n   121→        test_get_parts,\n   122→        test_search_vendors,\n   123→        test_order_not_found,\n   124→        test_jsf_page,\n   125→    ]\n   126→\n   127→    passed = 0\n   128→    failed = 0\n   129→    for test in tests:\n   130→        try:\n   131→            test()\n   132→            passed += 1\n   133→        except AssertionError as e:\n   134→            print(f\"FAIL: {test.__name__}: {e}\")\n   135→            failed += 1\n   136→        except Exception as e:\n   137→            print(f\"ERROR: {test.__name__}: {e}\")\n   138→            failed += 1\n   139→\n   140→    print(f\"\\nResults: {passed} passed, {failed} failed out of {len(tests)}\")\n   141→    sys.exit(0 if failed == 0 else 1)\n   142→\n   143→\n   144→if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n   145→    main()\n   146→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"5f6d709f-6122-4f36-9ebd-140923f7c1de"}
