{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PyTnUkqWpMbRLiuQQLLkbt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Date;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→\n     9→@IdClass(PartKey.class)\n    10→@Entity\n    11→@Table(name=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_PART\")\n    12→@SecondaryTable(name=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_PART_DETAIL\", pkJoinColumns={\n    13→   @PrimaryKeyJoinColumn(name=\"PARTNUMBER\", referencedColumnName=\"PARTNUMBER\"),\n    14→   @PrimaryKeyJoinColumn(name=\"REVISION\", referencedColumnName=\"REVISION\")\n    15→})\n    16→@NamedQuery(name=\"findAllParts\",\n    17→    query=\"SELECT p FROM Part p ORDER BY p.partNumber\")\n    18→public class Part implements Serializable {\n    19→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -3082087016342644227L;\n    20→\n    21→    private String partNumber;\n    22→    private int revision;\n    23→    private String description;\n    24→    private Date revisionDate;\n    25→    private Serializable drawing;\n    26→    private String specification;\n    27→    private Part bomPart;\n    28→    private List<Part> parts = new ArrayList<>();\n    29→    private VendorPart vendorPart;\n    30→\n    31→    public Part() {}\n    32→\n    33→    public Part(String partNumber, int revision, String description,\n    34→                Date revisionDate, String specification, Serializable drawing) {\n    35→        this.partNumber = partNumber;\n    36→        this.revision = revision;\n    37→        this.description = description;\n    38→        this.revisionDate = revisionDate;\n    39→        this.specification = specification;\n    40→        this.drawing = drawing;\n    41→    }\n    42→\n    43→    @Id @Column(nullable=false)\n    44→    public String getPartNumber() { return partNumber; }\n    45→    public void setPartNumber(String partNumber) { this.partNumber = partNumber; }\n    46→\n    47→    @Id @Column(nullable=false)\n    48→    public int getRevision() { return revision; }\n    49→    public void setRevision(int revision) { this.revision = revision; }\n    50→\n    51→    public String getDescription() { return description; }\n    52→    public void setDescription(String description) { this.description = description; }\n    53→\n    54→    @Temporal(TemporalType.DATE)\n    55→    public Date getRevisionDate() { return revisionDate; }\n    56→    public void setRevisionDate(Date revisionDate) { this.revisionDate = revisionDate; }\n    57→\n    58→    @Lob @Basic(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    59→    @Column(table=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_PART_DETAIL\")\n    60→    public Serializable getDrawing() { return drawing; }\n    61→    public void setDrawing(Serializable drawing) { this.drawing = drawing; }\n    62→\n    63→    @Lob @Basic(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    64→    @Column(table=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_PART_DETAIL\")\n    65→    public String getSpecification() { return specification; }\n    66→    public void setSpecification(String specification) { this.specification = specification; }\n    67→\n    68→    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    69→    @JoinColumns({\n    70→        @JoinColumn(name=\"BOMPARTNUMBER\", referencedColumnName=\"PARTNUMBER\"),\n    71→        @JoinColumn(name=\"BOMREVISION\", referencedColumnName=\"REVISION\")\n    72→    })\n    73→    public Part getBomPart() { return bomPart; }\n    74→    public void setBomPart(Part bomPart) { this.bomPart = bomPart; }\n    75→\n    76→    @OneToMany(mappedBy=\"bomPart\")\n    77→    public List<Part> getParts() { return parts; }\n    78→    public void setParts(List<Part> parts) { this.parts = parts; }\n    79→\n    80→    @OneToOne(mappedBy=\"part\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    81→    public VendorPart getVendorPart() { return vendorPart; }\n    82→    public void setVendorPart(VendorPart vendorPart) { this.vendorPart = vendorPart; }\n    83→}\n    84→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LBjHr9AyPdvbPG2Luds2FN","session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"1f51f474-477b-4faa-b09e-f084e3119348"}
