{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JQTLRrB4poAeFphovDJhw6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→\n     5→public final class LineItemKey implements Serializable {\n     6→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1562260205094677677L;\n     7→    private Integer customerOrder;\n     8→    private int itemId;\n     9→\n    10→    public LineItemKey() {\n    11→    }\n    12→\n    13→    public LineItemKey(Integer order, int itemId) {\n    14→        this.setCustomerOrder(order);\n    15→        this.setItemId(itemId);\n    16→    }\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public int hashCode() {\n    20→        return ((this.getCustomerOrder() == null\n    21→                ? 0 : this.getCustomerOrder().hashCode())\n    22→                ^ ((int) this.getItemId()));\n    23→    }\n    24→\n    25→    @Override\n    26→    public boolean equals(Object otherOb) {\n    27→        if (this == otherOb) {\n    28→            return true;\n    29→        }\n    30→        if (!(otherOb instanceof LineItemKey)) {\n    31→            return false;\n    32→        }\n    33→        LineItemKey other = (LineItemKey) otherOb;\n    34→        return ((this.getCustomerOrder() == null\n    35→                ? other.getCustomerOrder() == null : this.getCustomerOrder()\n    36→                .equals(other.getCustomerOrder()))\n    37→                && (this.getItemId() == other.getItemId()));\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    @Override\n    41→    public String toString() {\n    42→        return \"\" + getCustomerOrder() + \"-\" + getItemId();\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    public Integer getCustomerOrder() {\n    46→        return customerOrder;\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    public void setCustomerOrder(Integer order) {\n    50→        this.customerOrder = order;\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    public int getItemId() {\n    54→        return itemId;\n    55→    }\n    56→\n    57→    public void setItemId(int itemId) {\n    58→        this.itemId = itemId;\n    59→    }\n    60→}\n    61→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LBjHr9AyPdvbPG2Luds2FN","session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"1c28b466-6d0a-41c6-a90e-e2870c429626"}
