{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RySRFGPkrXRmsyj2QUWJqH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collection;\n     7→import java.util.Date;\n     8→\n     9→@Entity\n    10→@Table(name=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_CUSTOMERORDER\")\n    11→@NamedQuery(\n    12→    name=\"findAllOrders\",\n    13→    query=\"SELECT co FROM CustomerOrder co \" +\n    14→          \"ORDER BY co.orderId\"\n    15→)\n    16→public class CustomerOrder implements Serializable {\n    17→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 6582105865012174694L;\n    18→\n    19→    private Integer orderId;\n    20→    private char status;\n    21→    private Date lastUpdate;\n    22→    private int discount;\n    23→    private String shipmentInfo;\n    24→    private Collection<LineItem> lineItems = new ArrayList<>();\n    25→\n    26→    public CustomerOrder() {\n    27→        this.lastUpdate = new Date();\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    public CustomerOrder(Integer orderId, char status, int discount, \n    31→            String shipmentInfo) {\n    32→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    33→        this.status = status;\n    34→        this.discount = discount;\n    35→        this.shipmentInfo = shipmentInfo;\n    36→        this.lastUpdate = new Date();\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    @Id\n    40→    public Integer getOrderId() {\n    41→        return orderId;\n    42→    }\n    43→    \n    44→    public void setOrderId(Integer orderId) {\n    45→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    public char getStatus() {\n    49→        return status;\n    50→    }\n    51→    \n    52→    public void setStatus(char status) {\n    53→        this.status = status;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    57→    public Date getLastUpdate() {\n    58→        return lastUpdate;\n    59→    }\n    60→    \n    61→    public void setLastUpdate(Date lastUpdate) {\n    62→        this.lastUpdate = lastUpdate;\n    63→    }\n    64→\n    65→    public int getDiscount() {\n    66→        return discount;\n    67→    }\n    68→    \n    69→    public void setDiscount(int discount) {\n    70→        this.discount = discount;\n    71→    }\n    72→\n    73→    public String getShipmentInfo() {\n    74→        return shipmentInfo;\n    75→    }\n    76→    \n    77→    public void setShipmentInfo(String shipmentInfo) {\n    78→        this.shipmentInfo = shipmentInfo;\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL, mappedBy = \"customerOrder\", orphanRemoval = true)\n    82→    public Collection<LineItem> getLineItems() {\n    83→        return lineItems;\n    84→    }\n    85→    \n    86→    public void setLineItems(Collection<LineItem> lineItems) {\n    87→        this.lineItems = lineItems;\n    88→    }\n    89→\n    90→    public double calculateAmmount() {\n    91→        double amount = 0;\n    92→        for (LineItem item : getLineItems()) {\n    93→            if (item.getVendorPart() != null) {\n    94→                amount += item.getVendorPart().getPrice() * item.getQuantity();\n    95→            }\n    96→        }\n    97→        return (amount * (100 - getDiscount())) / 100.0;\n    98→    }\n    99→\n   100→    public double calculateAmount() {\n   101→        return calculateAmmount();\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    public void addLineItem(LineItem lineItem) {\n   105→        lineItem.setCustomerOrder(this);\n   106→        this.getLineItems().add(lineItem);\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    @Transient\n   110→    public int getNextId() {\n   111→        return this.lineItems.size() + 1;\n   112→    }\n   113→\n   114→    @PrePersist\n   115→    @PreUpdate\n   116→    private void touchLastUpdate() {\n   117→        this.lastUpdate = new Date();\n   118→    }\n   119→}\n   120→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LBjHr9AyPdvbPG2Luds2FN","session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"050a030c-5d27-41c1-b040-bd7c0bdc9ece"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-3-5-haiku-20241022","id":"msg_bdrk_01Ca4BzTRAT8WyXbQuVG6FLA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01RwkxRWmRadHi9DmHYt7NWS","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__persistence__order__spring__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/example/orderspring/entity/VendorPart.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1426,"cache_read_input_tokens":12199,"output_tokens":117},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LBjHr9AyPdvbPG2Luds2FN","session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"110b5572-aa17-441a-92a8-31c75a62c8ae"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RwkxRWmRadHi9DmHYt7NWS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→\n     6→@Entity\n     7→@Table(\n     8→    name = \"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_VENDOR_PART\",\n     9→    uniqueConstraints = @UniqueConstraint(columnNames = {\"PARTNUMBER\", \"PARTREVISION\"})\n    10→)\n    11→@NamedQueries({\n    12→    @NamedQuery(name = \"findAverageVendorPartPrice\",\n    13→        query = \"SELECT AVG(vp.price) FROM VendorPart vp\"),\n    14→    @NamedQuery(name = \"findTotalVendorPartPricePerVendor\",\n    15→        query = \"SELECT SUM(vp.price) FROM VendorPart vp WHERE vp.vendor.vendorId = :id\"),\n    16→    @NamedQuery(name = \"findAllVendorParts\",\n    17→        query = \"SELECT vp FROM VendorPart vp ORDER BY vp.vendorPartNumber\")\n    18→})\n    19→public class VendorPart implements Serializable {\n    20→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 4685631589912848921L;\n    21→\n    22→    private Long vendorPartNumber;\n    23→    private String description;\n    24→    private double price;\n    25→    private Part part;\n    26→    private Vendor vendor;\n    27→\n    28→    public VendorPart() {}\n    29→\n    30→    public VendorPart(String description, double price, Part part) {\n    31→        this.description = description;\n    32→        this.price = price;\n    33→        setPart(part);\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    @TableGenerator(\n    37→        name = \"vendorPartGen\",\n    38→        table = \"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_SEQUENCE_GENERATOR\",\n    39→        pkColumnName = \"GEN_KEY\",\n    40→        valueColumnName = \"GEN_VALUE\",\n    41→        pkColumnValue = \"VENDOR_PART_ID\",\n    42→        allocationSize = 10\n    43→    )\n    44→    @Id\n    45→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.TABLE, generator = \"vendorPartGen\")\n    46→    public Long getVendorPartNumber() { return vendorPartNumber; }\n    47→    public void setVendorPartNumber(Long vendorPartNumber) { this.vendorPartNumber = vendorPartNumber; }\n    48→\n    49→    public String getDescription() { return description; }\n    50→    public void setDescription(String description) { this.description = description; }\n    51→\n    52→    public double getPrice() { return price; }\n    53→    public void setPrice(double price) { this.price = price; }\n    54→\n    55→    @OneToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    56→    @JoinColumns({\n    57→        @JoinColumn(name = \"PARTNUMBER\", referencedColumnName = \"PARTNUMBER\"),\n    58→        @JoinColumn(name = \"PARTREVISION\", referencedColumnName = \"REVISION\")\n    59→    })\n    60→    public Part getPart() { return part; }\n    61→    public void setPart(Part part) {\n    62→        this.part = part;\n    63→        if (part != null && part.getVendorPart() != this) {\n    64→            part.setVendorPart(this);\n    65→        }\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    69→    @JoinColumn(name = \"VENDORID\")\n    70→    public Vendor getVendor() { return vendor; }\n    71→    public void setVendor(Vendor vendor) { this.vendor = vendor; }\n    72→}\n    73→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LBjHr9AyPdvbPG2Luds2FN","session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"2907b6b3-d6ea-418e-8219-801f2f5e6ab1"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-3-5-haiku-20241022","id":"msg_bdrk_013ffPQufv7ccfHRNR3dypwh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01UWistZJVJAuxgbrtvaEyGj","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__persistence__order__spring__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/example/orderspring/entity/Vendor.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1234,"cache_read_input_tokens":13625,"output_tokens":114},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LBjHr9AyPdvbPG2Luds2FN","session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"4327f627-ad8d-457d-a211-702a58d44a67"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UWistZJVJAuxgbrtvaEyGj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collection;\n     7→\n     8→@Entity\n     9→@Table(name=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_VENDOR\")\n    10→@NamedQueries({\n    11→  @NamedQuery(name=\"findVendorsByPartialName\",\n    12→              query=\"SELECT v FROM Vendor v WHERE LOCATE(:name, v.name) > 0\"),\n    13→  @NamedQuery(name=\"findVendorByCustomerOrder\",\n    14→              query=\"SELECT DISTINCT l.vendorPart.vendor FROM CustomerOrder co, IN(co.lineItems) l WHERE co.orderId = :id ORDER BY l.vendorPart.vendor.name\")\n    15→})\n    16→public class Vendor implements Serializable {\n    17→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 2538635007598426330L;\n    18→\n    19→    private int vendorId;\n    20→    private String name;\n    21→    private String address;\n    22→    private String contact;\n    23→    private String phone;\n    24→    private Collection<VendorPart> vendorParts = new ArrayList<>();\n    25→\n    26→    public Vendor() {}\n    27→    public Vendor(int vendorId, String name, String address, String contact, String phone) {\n    28→        this.vendorId = vendorId; this.name = name; this.address = address;\n    29→        this.contact = contact; this.phone = phone;\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    @Id\n    33→    public int getVendorId() { return vendorId; }\n    34→    public void setVendorId(int vendorId) { this.vendorId = vendorId; }\n    35→\n    36→    @Column(name=\"VENDORNAME\")\n    37→    public String getName() { return name; }\n    38→    public void setName(String name) { this.name = name; }\n    39→\n    40→    public String getAddress() { return address; }\n    41→    public void setAddress(String address) { this.address = address; }\n    42→\n    43→    public String getContact() { return contact; }\n    44→    public void setContact(String contact) { this.contact = contact; }\n    45→\n    46→    public String getPhone() { return phone; }\n    47→    public void setPhone(String phone) { this.phone = phone; }\n    48→\n    49→    @OneToMany(cascade=CascadeType.ALL, mappedBy=\"vendor\", orphanRemoval = true)\n    50→    public Collection<VendorPart> getVendorParts() { return vendorParts; }\n    51→    public void setVendorParts(Collection<VendorPart> vendorParts) { this.vendorParts = vendorParts; }\n    52→\n    53→    public void addVendorPart(VendorPart vendorPart) {\n    54→        vendorPart.setVendor(this);        // keep both sides in sync\n    55→        getVendorParts().add(vendorPart);\n    56→    }\n    57→}\n    58→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LBjHr9AyPdvbPG2Luds2FN","session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"cb1cae24-5510-489f-bc82-2ba4343271f9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LBjHr9AyPdvbPG2Luds2FN","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the analysis of the entity files, here's a comprehensive breakdown:\n\n1. Part.java\n   - Class Name: Part\n   - @Entity: Yes\n   - @Table: PERSISTENCE_ORDER_PART\n   - @IdClass: PartKey (composite key with partNumber and revision)\n   - Key Fields: \n     - @Id partNumber (String)\n     - @Id revision (int)\n   - Relationships:\n     - @ManyToOne with itself (bomPart)\n     - @OneToMany with itself (parts)\n     - @OneToOne with VendorPart\n   - Spring Imports: No (uses Jakarta Persistence)\n\n2. PartKey.java\n   - Not an entity, but a composite key class for Part\n   - Implements Serializable\n   - Contains partNumber and revision\n   - Overrides hashCode(), equals(), and toString()\n\n3. LineItemKey.java\n   - Not an entity, but a composite key class for LineItem\n   - Implements Serializable\n   - Contains customerOrder and itemId\n   - Overrides hashCode(), equals(), and toString()\n\n4. LineItem.java\n   - Class Name: LineItem\n   - @Entity: Yes\n   - @Table: PERSISTENCE_ORDER_LINEITEM\n   - @IdClass: LineItemKey (composite key with itemId and customerOrder)\n   - Key Fields:\n     - @Id itemId (int)\n     - @Id customerOrder (CustomerOrder)\n   - Relationships:\n     - @ManyToOne with VendorPart\n     - @ManyToOne with CustomerOrder\n   - Spring Imports: No (uses Jakarta Persistence)\n\n5. CustomerOrder.java\n   - Class Name: CustomerOrder\n   - @Entity: Yes\n   - @Table: PERSISTENCE_ORDER_CUSTOMERORDER\n   - Key Field:\n     - @Id orderId (Integer)\n   - Relationships:\n     - @OneToMany with LineItem (cascade, orphanRemoval)\n   - Spring Imports: No (uses Jakarta Persistence)\n\n6. VendorPart.java\n   - Class Name: VendorPart\n   - @Entity: Yes\n   - @Table: PERSISTENCE_ORDER_VENDOR_PART\n   - Key Field:\n     - @Id @GeneratedValue vendorPartNumber (Long)\n   - Relationships:\n     - @OneToOne with Part\n     - @ManyToOne with Vendor\n   - Spring Imports: No (uses Jakarta Persistence)\n\n7. Vendor.java\n   - Class Name: Vendor\n   - @Entity: Yes\n   - @Table: PERSISTENCE_ORDER_VENDOR\n   - Key Field:\n     - @Id vendorId (int)\n   - Relationships:\n     - @OneToMany with VendorPart (cascade, orphanRemoval)\n   - Spring Imports: No (uses Jakarta Persistence)\n\nNotable Observations:\n- All entities use Jakarta Persistence annotations (jakarta.persistence)\n- No remaining Spring-specific imports\n- Complex relationships between entities (Part-VendorPart, CustomerOrder-LineItem, Vendor-VendorPart)\n- Most entities implement Serializable\n- Use of composite keys with separate key classes (PartKey, LineItemKey)\n- Extensive use of named queries for each entity"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"1d18b3eb-e820-4e0d-8895-8dadc9a43ffb"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01ULRXppZ5rHWLNVJw4HdLeN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good - all entities are clean Jakarta Persistence. Now there's a key issue I need to address: the `DataInitializationService` uses BMT with `UserTransaction`, but `OrderService` is `@Stateless` (CMT by default). When `DataInitializationService` calls `orderService.createPart()` etc., those calls will join the existing BMT transaction. However, the `OrderService.createOrder()` method can throw `RuntimeException` which in CMT would mark the transaction for rollback. But since we're using BMT in the caller and the OrderService is CMT, the nested calls WILL join the BMT transaction - this should work.\n\nLet me check another potential issue - the `DataInitializationService` calls `orderService.addPartToBillOfMaterial()` which calls `partRepository.save(bom)` and `partRepository.save(part)` - which both try to merge. Since the entities were persisted earlier in the same transaction but the repos do `em.find()` then decide persist vs merge, this should work since the entities will be in the persistence context.\n\nLet me now rebuild and test:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1063,"cache_read_input_tokens":47442,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1063,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":410},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c75ef7e1-cdcb-4fc9-ba4d-53d982e17ac3","uuid":"c155df34-7221-4fca-98d1-c42a151446dc"}
